COMMERCIAL LICENCE REQUIRED

The following uses require a written commercial licence agreement obtained
from the author before use:

1. Enterprise Use
   Any Enterprise (as defined above) using the Software internally, in
   products, or in services must hold a valid commercial licence.

2. Embedding in Commercial Products
   Embedding the Software in a hardware device, firmware image, appliance,
   or platform that is sold or licensed to third parties requires a
   commercial licence, regardless of company size.

3. Managed Service / SaaS
   Operating the Software as a cloud-hosted or managed service offered to
   third parties requires a commercial licence.

4. OEM / White-Label Distribution
   Redistributing the Software as part of a commercial offering under a
   different name or brand requires a commercial licence.

---

HOW TO OBTAIN A COMMERCIAL LICENCE

Contact: sridharan.thangaraji@protonmail.com
Subject: RogueOS Commercial Licence Enquiry

Please include:
  - Your organisation name and annual revenue range
  - Intended use (internal tooling / product / SaaS / embedded / other)
  - Approximate number of users or deployments

Licences are priced fairly. The goal is to support continued development,
not to be a barrier. Small studios, indie companies, and early-stage
startups are encouraged to reach out — there is room to talk.

